# ── Encryption model ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Committed  : media.json.age, media-age/<uuid>.age, key.age (passphrase-wrapped
#              private key), .age-recipient (public key, not secret).
# Never commit: the plaintext key, the plaintext manifest, or decrypted media.

key.txt                # decrypted private identity — the secret that unlocks everything
*.identity
media.json             # decrypted manifest
media/                 # decrypted working copies of all media

# ── Raw media (belt and braces) ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# media/ is already ignored, but ignore stray plaintext media anywhere too, so a
# file dropped at the repo root can never be committed unencrypted. A name
# ending in .age does not match these, so the encrypted copies still commit.
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.png
*.gif
*.webp
*.bmp
*.tif
*.tiff
*.heic
*.heif
*.avif
*.mov
*.mp4
*.m4v
*.webm
*.avi
*.mkv
*.mpg
*.mpeg
*.wmv
*.flv

# ── Secrets / local-only ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.catbox-userhash

# ── macOS / editor cruft ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
*.swp
*~
node_modules/
